      "note": "Attestation#role is descriptive metadata identifying the attester (control_owner, isso, ciso, etc.), NOT an app-level authorization role. Defense-in-depth: app/models/attestation.rb adds `validates :role, inclusion: { in: ROLES }` so mass-assignment cannot set arbitrary values; only the controlled vocabulary in Attestation::ROLES is accepted. Same rationale applies to :frequency (FREQUENCIES inclusion) and :status (STATUSES inclusion) added in #440. The Brakeman BRAKE0105 warning fires because the field name 'role' is on its dangerous-key list, not because the assignment is actually unsafe."
    },
