      "note": "Admin::ServiceAccountsController#service_account_params permits :admin BY DESIGN. This is the admin-only service-account admin interface (module Admin, admin-gated) and granting admin to a service account is an intentional, documented feature — the 'Grant admin privileges' checkbox (see spec/system/admin_service_account_admin_checkbox_spec.rb), called out in the model header as AC-6 'admin flag is per-SA opt-in, never implicit'. Brakeman flags :admin because it's on its dangerous-key list; the assignment is safe here because it is reachable only by an authenticated admin. Unlike the Attestation permits there is no value-bounding validator (:admin is a boolean); the safety rests on the admin-only namespace + intended capability."
    },
